race.comment: TAN TAT DELIGHT (14) found the blackbook of many after her debut at Kyneton, when she was stuck three back the fence and didn't get out until well into the straight before charging to the line to be beaten just half-a-length. The inside was inferior ground that day, too, which only added to the performance. She only needs to run up to that to break the maiden here. ECO EXPRESS (3) was never really a factor on debut but that race was won by a handy one and the runner-up won at Ballarat on Thursday, so the form's held up. OCTANE REIGN (5) could be an improver in blinkers, which sparked a good showing in a recent jumpout. It might pay to forgive SPARKLING AWARD (13) the ordinary debut because it was on Heavy ground and she did beat TAN TAT DELIGHT in a jumpout prior. ROGUE WARRIOR (6) has been gelded since the debut and has the draw to run an improved race.
